<section id="faq" class="section">
	<div class="container">
		<h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
		<div class="faq-content">
			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">What is Mac Remote Controller?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>Mac Remote Controller is a companion app that allows you to control your Mac computer remotely from your Android phone. It provides seamless integration between your Mac and mobile device, enabling you to manage media playback, volume, applications, files, and system settings from anywhere in your home or office.</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">How does Mac Remote Controller work?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>Mac Remote Controller works by connecting your Android phone and Mac over the same local Wi-Fi network or mobile hotspot. After installing the Mac companion app and pairing your devices via QR code, the app establishes a secure connection that allows you to send commands and control your Mac remotely.</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">What features does Mac Remote Controller offer?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>Mac Remote Controller offers comprehensive remote control features including:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Smart app following that adapts to your active Mac applications</li>
						<li>Media playback control (play, pause, skip tracks)</li>
						<li>Volume and brightness adjustment</li>
						<li>File and workspace management</li>
						<li>Integration with applications you have installed on your Mac</li>
						<li>Window management and keyboard input</li>
						<li>Secure encrypted authentication</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">Is Mac Remote Controller free to use?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>Yes, Mac Remote Controller is free to download and use. The app offers core functionality at no cost. Some advanced features may be available through optional in-app purchases for users who want enhanced capabilities.</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">What are the system requirements?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>To use Mac Remote Controller, you need:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>An Android phone running Android 5.0 or later</li>
						<li>A Mac computer running macOS 10.13 or later</li>
						<li>Both devices connected to the same Wi-Fi network, or use your mobile hotspot</li>
						<li>The Mac companion desktop app installed on your Mac</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">Is my data secure when using Mac Remote Controller?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>Yes, Mac Remote Controller prioritizes security. The app uses encrypted authentication to ensure secure local network communication. All data transmission happens over your local network, and no data is sent to external servers. The connection is established directly between your phone and Mac.</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">Can I use Mac Remote Controller outside my home network?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>Mac Remote Controller is designed to work over local networks (Wi-Fi or mobile hotspot). For remote access outside your local network, you would need to set up additional network configuration such as VPN or port forwarding, which is not officially supported by the app.</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">Which applications does Mac Remote Controller integrate with?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>Mac Remote Controller interacts with the applications you have installed on your Mac. The app provides dedicated controls and adapts its interface based on the active application on your Mac, offering context-aware functionality for apps like Spotify (media playback control), Chrome (browser navigation and tab management), Microsoft Teams (meeting controls and productivity features), and Finder (file management and workspace organization).</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">How do I pair my phone with my Mac?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>To pair your devices:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Install the Mac companion app on your Mac</li>
						<li>Open the Mac app and click the "Pair" button</li>
						<li>A QR code will be displayed on your Mac screen</li>
						<li>Open the Mac Remote Controller app on your Android phone</li>
						<li>Tap "Connect" and scan the QR code with your phone's camera</li>
						<li>The devices will be paired and ready to use</li>
					</ol>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="faq-item">
				<h3 class="faq-question">Does Mac Remote Controller work with iPhone or iPad?</h3>
				<div class="faq-answer">
					<p>Currently, Mac Remote Controller is available for Android devices only. There is no iOS version available at this time. The app is specifically designed for Android phones to control Mac computers.</p>
				</div>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

